Start from Dossier_Terrain:
“Give me dossiers BUT only if they have a notaire that matches condition

NO RELATION (same table)

👉 You search only in one table

✔ Method: where()
public function search($id)
{
    $data = Dossier_Terrain::where('iddossier', $id)->get();

    return view('result', compact('data'));
}
When do we use this?
search by name
search by id
filter in same table

WITH RELATION (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 You search using another table

✔ Method: whereHas()
public function search($id_cab)
{
    $data = Dossier_Terrain::whereHas('notaire', function($q) use ($id_cab) {
        $q->where('id_cab', $id_cab);
    })->get();

    return view('result', compact('data'));
}
When do we use this?
filter dossiers by notaire
filter orders by user
filter students by class

👉 THERE IS RELATION
3. WHEN YOU WANT DATA + RELATION (NO FILTER)

👉 You just want to display related data

✔ Method: with():
public function list()
{
    $data = Dossier_Terrain::with('notaire')->get();

    return view('list', compact('data'));
}
show dossier + notaire name
show product + category
show order + user
Ask yourself:
1. Same table?

👉 use where()

2. Related table filter?

👉 use whereHas()

3. Just display relation?

👉 use with()
Easy memory
Situation	Method
same table search	where()
search through relation	whereHas()
display relation data	with()
